parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seatbelt buckle can lead to a lack of restraint in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seatbelt buckle will not fasten
the seatbelt buckle latch fails
the seatbelt fails to retract
the seatbelt does not properly restrain the occupant.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The peeling or flaking off of the paint can lead to rust and corrosion, compromising the structural integrity of the vehicle and potentially causing safety issues.
symptoms: Paint peels or flakes off
exposing the primer or underlying metal
uneven paint finish
rust or corrosion spots.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can lead to a loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS warning light illuminates on the dashboard
the brake pedal goes to the floor with no response from the brakes
the vehicle experiences unintended acceleration or deceleration
the brake system warning light comes on while driving
the brakes do not feel as though they are applied despite the warning light being on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driveshaft can cause a loss of vehicle power, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences a sudden loss of power
the driveshaft breaks or seizes
the vehicle makes a loud noise or vibration
the vehicle is unable to move.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Driveshaft Corrosion due to Moisture Ingress
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Moisture ingress into the driveshaft can cause corrosion, leading to driveshaft failure, which can result in a loss of vehicle power and control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The driveshaft shows signs of corrosion
rust
or wear
the vehicle experiences a gradual loss of power
the driveshaft makes a noise or vibration
the vehicle is unable to move.
